The Herald London. — Zimbabwean midfielder Michael Ndiweni has been offered a professional contract by English Premier League side Newcastle. The 18-year-old was offered the deal with five other second-year scholars. A Newcastle statement reads: “At Under-18 level, second-year scholars Harry Barclay, Kyle Crossley, James Huntley, Jamie Miley, Michael Ndiweni and Joshua Stewart have all been offered professional contracts, while Piotr Banda, Liam Chrystal, Joel Green, Josh Nicholson and Nathan Robertson will leave the academy this summer.” The midfielder had an impressive campaign with the Newcastle United Academy, scoring 13 goals in 18 games. His performance caught the eye of coach Eddie Howe and the youngster was called up to train with the senior team in March. Ndiweni was born in England to Zimbabwean parents and is eligible to play for both England and Zimbabwe. His father coaches youth football in Newcastle.  — soccer24.